column1:
Sorry about that—we just despise the police,
is all.

It's kinda weird when you say it with a smile
like that...
We'd appreciate it if you'd get to the point.

Fine, fine, I'll skip the runaround and just
tell you.

I'm Zenkichi Hasegawa, an investigator on
loan to Tokyo's Public Security branch.

I'm officially an Inspector. It's not a rank to
sneeze at.

Inspectors are not to be sneezed at.
Okay, I've got it.

*sigh* Whatever. [1B]S0, I need to
ask you something.

Did you hear at all about that mess on the chat
show the other day? With Alice Hiiragi?
Yeah, of course you did. It was a huge disaster.

I can't believe you just told me that... You sure
you're on the same page as them?

You're not good at playing stupid. Your face
already told me you knew.

Well, there's already been a full investigation
into the incident...

There was no indication the MC was planning
to propose—everyone questioned said he didn't
even know who Alice was before this week.

Not only that, he'd already been engaged to his
co-host for however long. There isn't a whiff of
motive to be found.

"Doesn't this sound like the work of the
Phantom Thieves?"

A whooole lot of similar cases last year, no?
Sudden personality shifts, abnormal behavior,
psychotic breakdowns...

If that MC went bonkers from a change of heart,
you're gonna be suspect number one:

...[1B]S2,
the leader of the Phantom Thieves of Hearts.

We don't know if it's drugs, or hypnosis, or
what, but they wanna charge you with criminal
mischief.
It's only a matter of time before you're arrested.
This is outrageous! What proof do you have?

Sure it's outrageous, but we don't actually have
any proof yet. That's why I'm here.
So, level with me. Are you?
Are you the one doing this?
Yeah... Yeah, that's what I thought.

Ah hello. Commissioner, yes, I'm with the
Phantom Thieves' leader.

I just asked for a confession, but he says he's
innocent... Yes, that's right, hahah.
Huh? Kidding? No, no, this is all real.

That's enough nonsense? Oh, okay...
I'm on my way to the office.

Well, as you saw, I reported what you said
to my boss...
But if you ask me, I don't think she's convinced.
Did he really call his boss?
Holy shit... What is WITH this guy?
What are you trying to prove here?

No matter how hard you claim to be innocent,
there are people out there chomping at the bit
to arrest you.

If that ever happens, you're done for—and I'll
be up the river too, 'cause then this case'll
never get solved.

So I wanted to make you an offer...
Or maybe, more like a deal.

I want to solve this case. To do that, I need
the intel you've gathered.

At the moment, I don't have anything that
even resembles a lead. I'm totally at a loss.

You though, you just don't wanna get arrested.
I can do what needs to be done so that won't
happen.

Bureau men are a trustworthy lot in the force.
There won't be any problems.
Sound like a fair deal to you?
That makes two of us, huh?

Well that sounds like a no... Although I can't
blame you, considering what you've been
through.

We don't have any reason why we should
trust you.

I appreciate you trying to see the benefit here.
I really don't think it's a bad deal for you.
Dude, hang on! You really think we should trust someone this shady?

You know how they say the wise cat hides its
claws? Let's just say that applies to me too.

You don't have to do anything until you
decide whether you trust him or not.
That sure is a noisy cat.

Well, I don't need an answer right away.
Get back to me once you think it over.

I hope you'll see things my way, Phantom
Thieves.
All right, Boss. Be back soon for some curry.
Sorry, the curry's eighty-sixed. For you.
